      "projectDescription": "Neurofibromin/NF1-depletion (NF1low) is associated with endocrine therapy resistance in approximately 20% of ER+/HER2\u2013 early-stage breast cancer but specific treatments for NF1low tumors are not established.  Proteogenomic analyses on ER+/HER2\u2013 breast cancer demonstrated that NF1low tumors exhibit elevated CDK4/6 activity.  NF1-silencing in cell lines promoted ER recruitment to CCND1, thus increasing cyclin-D1 levels.  Additionally, RAF is demonstrated to directly phosphorylate the CDK4 activation-loop (pT172) thus providing a direct connection between NF1 loss and an increase in CDK4 activity.  Consequently, NF1low cancer cells are differentially sensitive to a fulvestrant plus CDK4/6 inhibitor (CDK4/6i) combination, with cell-death induction in vitro, and durable tumor regressions in ER+ NF1low PDX models in vivo. Furthermore, NF1low ER+/HER2\u2013 tumors treated neoadjuvantly with 4 weeks of anastrozole exhibited a minimal reduction of a multigene mRNA proliferation score vs NF1high tumors but exhibited marked sensitivity to the subsequent addition of palbociclib. In conclusion, dual ER and downstream RAF activation following NF1-loss drives endocrine therapy resistance and CDK4/6i sensitivity in NF1low ER+ breast cancer.  NF1 status should therefore be prioritized for biomarker investigations in adjuvant CDK4/6i trials to determine whether the NF1low status",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "The in-vitro reaction sample was subjected to SDS-PAGE (NuPAGE 10% Bis-Tris Gel, Invitrogen). The target band from SDS-PAGE gel was excised and processed for in-gel digestion using trypsin enzyme (Pierce 90058). The tryptic peptides were resuspended in 15\uf06dl of loading solution (5% methanol containing 0.1% formic acid) and analyzed using nanoLC1200 system coupled to Orbitrap Fusion Lumos mass spectrometer (Thermo Scientific, San Jose, CA).",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "). The MS raw data was searched using Proteome Discoverer 1.4 software (Thermo Scientific, San Jose, CA) with Mascot algorithm (v2.4, Matrix Science) against the human NCBI refseq database (updated 2021_12_23). The precursor ion tolerance and product ion tolerance were set to 20ppm and 0.5Da respectively. Maximum cleavage of 2 with Trypsin enzyme, dynamic modification of oxidation (M), protein N-term acetylation, phosphorylation (S/T/Y) and deamidation (N/Q) was allowed. The peptides identified from mascot result file were validated with 5% false discover rate (FDR) in Percolator and subjected to manual verification for correct site assignment.",
